Lesson 

---------- [L1]

Video link: https://youtu.be/nP0iDvYXv6w
Audio link: https://rss.com/podcasts/footnerdprogram/560912/

Creators: Tom Williams, James Dooner

Framework:
- defining ground living 
- ground living as an antidote to sedentarism
- history of land animals and our relationship to the ground
- culture of comfort and convenience 
- anatomical discussion of hip and low back range of motion
- 



Audio lesson notes:
- detailed notes and timestamps from the audio lesson


Experiments (nano to macro)
- for the next 10 days, adopt the ground for your work hours
- record what the experience was like for you 
- share your story with your peers in nerd office hours or post in Slack
and/or
- explore the sit and rise assessment/screen for 10 days
- let the 1st day be the baseline screen, then practice for the remainder of the days and 
rescreen on day 10
- record your experience and share it with your peers in office hours or post in Slack



